CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 23, 1956, pg. 16 reads: "Lincoln Auxiliary - A committee of the Lincoln University Ladies Auxiliary of Pittsburgh, maps plans for a Garden Party July 1. Seated, left to right: Mrs. Marian B. Holmes, president, and Mrs. Jessie Shropshire.  Standing: Mrs. Jeanette French, Mrs. Hidayet Collington and Mrs. Norma Patrick. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five committee members of the Lincoln University Ladies Auxiliary of Pittsburgh, from left, seated: Marian B. Holmes and Jessie Shropshire; standing: Jeanette French, Hidayet Collington, and Norma Patrick, seated at table for meeting in the Greene Hearth
